{"TopicId":170612,"ForumId":15,"TopicTitle":"Emissive on Windows.","CreatedByName":"Starlord Kerman","CreatedById":177240,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-08T02:35:59Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Starlord Kerman","CreatedById":177240,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-08T02:35:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EHi all,\u00A0I have been working on a quick command pod just to get a feel for what goes into making a mod and I\u0027m having some trouble with the window lights. I\u0027ve been trying to use the\u00A0ModuleColorChanger method mentioned here:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed595513715\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/165413-emissive-on-windows/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:209px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EI can get the lights to kind of work if\u00A0I apply the\u00A0texture to the window mesh which I want to be visible when the lights are off and then include the ModuleColorChanger in the CFG file. This method, however, just makes the \u0022lights on\u0022 solid white.\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022B63Yl2i.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022293\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/B63Yl2i.gif\u0022 width=\u0022600\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I\u0027m having trouble with is that I can\u0027t seem to apply a texture to be visible when the lights are on (the black texture except for the lighted features). How do I apply both the \u0022lights off\u0022 and \u0022lights on\u0022 textures to the same part in Unity? Or do a make a duplicate of the window mesh? Here\u0027s the current hierarchy in unity:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022rTjy2SE.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/rTjy2SE.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022756\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CobaltWolf","CreatedById":105588,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-08T16:28:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/177240-starlord-kerman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022177240\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/177240-starlord-kerman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Starlord Kerman\u003C/a\u003E I always use this method, which lets you use an emissive texture. However, if I remember the stock part\u0027s window emissives look pretty much exactly like that gif you posted.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5926786027\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/135428-color-animation-editor/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}